com.facebook.react.views.swiperefresh

Class SwipeRefreshLayoutManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.react.bridge.BaseJavaModule
      • com.facebook.react.uimanager.ViewManager<T,C>
        • com.facebook.react.uimanager.BaseViewManager<T,LayoutShadowNode>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NativeModule, BaseViewManagerInterface<ReactSwipeRefreshLayout>, IViewManagerWithChildren, AndroidSwipeRefreshLayoutManagerInterface<ReactSwipeRefreshLayout>

    public class SwipeRefreshLayoutManager
extends ViewGroupManager<ReactSwipeRefreshLayout>
implements AndroidSwipeRefreshLayoutManagerInterface<ReactSwipeRefreshLayout>
    ViewManager for ReactSwipeRefreshLayout which allows the user to "pull to refresh" a child view. Emits an onRefresh event when this happens.

      • getExportedCustomDirectEventTypeConstants

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> getExportedCustomDirectEventTypeConstants()
        Description copied from class: ViewManager
        Returns a map of config data passed to JS that defines eligible events that can be placed on native views. This should return non-bubbling directly-dispatched event types.

        Returned map should be of the form: 

         {
   "onTwirl": {
     "registrationName": "onTwirl"
   }
 }
        Overrides:
        getExportedCustomDirectEventTypeConstants in class BaseViewManager<ReactSwipeRefreshLayout,LayoutShadowNode>

      • getDelegate

        protected ViewManagerDelegate<ReactSwipeRefreshLayout> getDelegate()
        Description copied from class: ViewManager
        Override this method and return an instance of ViewManagerDelegate if the props of the view managed by this view manager should be set via this delegate. The provided instance will then get calls to ViewManagerDelegate.setProperty(View, String, Object) for every prop that must be updated and it's the delegate's responsibility to apply these values to the view.

        By default this method returns null, which means that the view manager doesn't have a delegate and the view props should be set internally by the view manager itself.

        Overrides:
        getDelegate in class ViewManager<ReactSwipeRefreshLayout,LayoutShadowNode>
        Returns:
        an instance of ViewManagerDelegate if the props of the view managed by this view manager should be set via this delegate
